&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Garlic:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Garlic has near-deity status in Indian cuisine. It is used in paste form, to add flavor and thickness; tangy pack-a-punch chunks are sprinkled on meats; it is minced inside naan bread and sliced up in dips. Put simply, it&amp;rsquo;s more than your average seasoning.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;It Carries:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
